cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CG 

This paper involves the use of a computational model of Physarum, a biological organism, to approximate Voronoi diagrams using stimuli presented by repellent fields. This falls under the category of bio-inspired computing, which is often associated with the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the use of computational models and algorithms to mimic biological processes and behaviour is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social computing (cs.SI). The paper also involves the manipulation and analysis of data structures, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
